se.miun.itm.input.model.mapping

Class Wrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.miun.itm.input.model.mapping.Wrapper

  • public class Wrapper
extends java.lang.Object
    A wrapper is a class that allows numerical values to be wrapped for range definitions in the code mappings file. This is of importance because many third party frameworks have their own customized definitions of certain ranges, a prominent example is the Probability class of the apache maths uncommons.
    Author:
    Felix Dobslaw
